---

Wash and dry produce.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce}
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until pork begins to brown, ~{3%minutes} (it'll finish cooking
in the next step).

Meanwhile, break up @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size
pieces if necessary. Massage @microwavable rice{1%unit} in package to
break up grains.

Add another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan with pork. Add broccoli
and rice; season with a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}. Cover pan with #lid{}. Cook, undisturbed, until
broccoli is tender and pork is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @garlic-ginger scallion paste{2%ounce}.
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Lightly crush @peanuts{1/2%ounce} in their bag.

Divide pork and rice skillet between #bowls{}; top with peanuts and serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.